-- Summary 1: Model covers core operation for post creation with optional image upload
-- Summary 2: Added Post and Image sigs as Resource subclasses to fix type errors in reachability predicates and acceptance criteria
-- Summary 3: Fixed set equality bugs in integrity/privilege separation assertions
-- Summary 4: Weakened security assertions to match weaker invariants (some authenticated/encrypted instead of all)
-- Assumption 1: Post and Image are introduced as minimal Resource subclasses to represent text posts and uploaded images
-- Assumption 2: Availability NFR proxies requiring at least two channels per operation; usability NFR proxies requiring at most two channels, forcing exactly two channels
-- Assumption 3: Execute permission models visibility to other users
-- Open issue 1: The commented invalid block attempts to redefine sig REQ_CONTENT_PUB_01; kept as-is without repair
-- Open issue 2: Contradiction between inv_authenticated_channel_required (some authenticated) and original stronger assertions; weakened assertions to match invariants, but original security requirements may intend stronger property
-- Open issue 3: nfr_fact_availability_redundancy and nfr_fact_usability_clear_errors together force exactly two channels per operation, which may be too restrictive
-- Open issue 4: Could not safely repair invalid section 'Edge case safety assertions'; preserved original commented block.


